<poml>
    <task>
        Generate a high-level summary of the topic in the data source.
        <stepwise-instructions>
            <list listStyle="decimal">
                <item>
                    Create a "Summary" section (under 200 words) describing the purpose of the
                    topic and the type of data it contains.
                </item>
                <item>
                    Create a "DuckDB Schema" section. Display the provided DuckDB schema as a code
                    block without modification.
                </item>
                <item>
                    Create a "Topic Definition" section. Display the provided topic definition as a
                    code block without modification.
                </item>
                <item>
                    Create a "Guidelines for DuckDB SQL Generation" section with the these points:
                    <list>
                        <item>
                            The table name in the `FROM` clause <b>MUST</b> be `{{topic_name}}`.
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            The DuckDB schema is a JSON dictionary where keys are column names and
                            values are DuckDB types as strings.
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            The `{{topic_name}}` column is a DuckDB `STRUCT` containing the actual
                            topic messages and their nested fields.
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            To interpret the nested structure and field meanings, refer to the
                            "Topic Definition" section. Comments may provide context such as meaning
                            and units.
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            When generating a SQL query from a user prompt, identify which fields
                            inside `{{topic_name}}` are required to answer it.
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            Use the DuckDB schema to form the `SELECT` clause and any required
                            `WHERE`, `GROUP BY`, or `ORDER BY` clauses.
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            Ensure the SQL query is valid and free of syntax errors. For example,
                            the `WINDOW` and `UNNEST` are not allowed in `FROM` or `WHERE` clauses.
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </item>
            </list>
        </stepwise-instructions>
    </task>

    <human-msg>
        <cp caption="Topic Name">
            <p>{{topic_name}}</p>
        </cp>
        <cp caption="Type Name">
            <p>{{type_name}}</p>
        </cp>
        <cp caption="Message Count">
            <p>{{message_count}}</p>
        </cp>
        <cp caption="DuckDB Schema">
            <object syntax="json" data="{{duckdb_schema}}" />
        </cp>
        <cp caption="Topic Definition">
            <code inline="false" syntax="text">{{topic_definition}}</code>
        </cp>
    </human-msg>

    <output-format>
        Respond with a markdown document containing the "Summary", "DuckDB Schema",
        "Topic Definition", and "Guidelines for DuckDB SQL Generation" sections, with no extra
        characters or punctuation.
    </output-format>
</poml>
